item.note:
Translation: I am skeptical for my choice, that is why here I provide other choices available:
      I translate here አጐለትኩ፡አክሰምኩ፡ወአምነይኩ as 'I have assinged gwǝlt, dedicated, secluded',
      while the translation found in Roger Schneider's archive offers 'I have given gult, and I have dignified and sanctified', while Derat (p.57) offers 'j'ai donné en gwǝlt, j'ai assingné et j'ai délimité';
    ወሀብኩ፡ለመጣዕ፡ዘአሀም I translate here as 'I granted', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'I have given', Derat - as 'j'ai donné';
ምስለ፡ምድሮሙ፡በንጽፉ፡ወበቀልቀላ፡ዓጋማ I translate here as 'including their lands ʿĀgāmā's steep', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'with their fields, and at its limit and endge Āgmā', while Derat offers 'avec leur terres, à la limite et au ravin d'Agāmā;
ዘኢይበውእ፡ I translate here as 'nor... should interfere', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'nor... shall enter', Derat offers 'n'entre pas';
ዘአልቦ፡ግብረ፡ለባዕድ፡ዘእንበለ፡አበ፡ምኔት፡ዘመጣዕ I translate here as 'where no other tax from anyone [sould be] set apart from',  Roger Schneider's translator - as 'It owes no tribute to an outsider', Derat offers 'sans taxes pour l'étranger';
ለዝንቱ፡ጕልት፡ወለዝንቱ፡ክሱም፡ውጉዘ፡ለይኩን I translate here as '... this gwǝlt, and this kǝsum, may he be excommunicated', Roger Schneider's translator - as 'this gult and dignity... may he be anathematized', while Derat offers 'ce gwǝlt et cette assignation soit excommunié'.

Translation:
 I translate ወሀብኩ as 'I granted', while Roger Schneider's translator offers 'I have given';
ወከመ፡ይግበሩ፡ተዝካሮ፡ለመጣዕ as 'so that they celebrate the commemoration of Maṭāʿ', while Roger Schneider's translator offers 'so that they may celebrate the commemoration';
ከመ፡ይትወሀሰኒ as 'so that he would beseech a reward for me for me', while Roger Scheider's translator offers 'so that he may be my garantor';
እመቦ፡ዘተኀየሎ፡ወዘአገሎ፡ as 'If there is someone who would violate it or defraud it', while Roger Schneider's translator offers 'whosoever breaks or intringes this'.

ab.note:
Roger Schneider's translator, as he used the edited text by Conti Rossini, translated
  በ፭፻፡ወ፯፡ዓመተ፡ምሕረት, what I translate as 'In the 507th year of Mercy' as 'In the Year of Mercy 506.'
in ስዩመ፡ዘሬዳ the translator interprets ዘ as an element to express a genitive case relationship:
thus, what I translate as 'sǝyum of Zaredā Zarʾa Dāwit' he translates as 'the governor of Redā'.
ኢትንሥኦ፡እግዚኦ፡በመዋዕለ፡ውርዙቱ፡ለእግዚእየ፡ዐምደ፡ጽዮን, which I translate as 'Do not abandon, o Lord, my Lord ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon in the days of his youth' he translates as 'Do not abandor my lord ʿĀmda Ṣǝyon in the days of his youth'.
There are other cases, which should be rather discussed for my choice is dubious:
  ከመ፡ይትወኀሰኒ, which I tranlate as 'would beseech a reward for me', he translates as 'may be my guarantor'; ዘኢይበኦ, which I translate as 'should not penestrate' he translates more literally (may be correctly)'shall enter';
  ኢዘነገሠ፡ወኢዘአንገስገሰ, which I translate as 'neither the one who reigns nor who is agitated' he translates as 'neither the one who is made king nor the one who made king';
  ቃል፡ነጋሲ፡ወኢደቀ፡ጽርኅ, which I translate as 'neither the spokesman of nǝguś, nor children of the palace' he translates as 'neither the proxy of the king nor the pages (I am not sure about my interpretation for it makes little sense for me) of the palace';
  ወለእመቦ፡ዘተአገለ, which I traslate as 'if there is anyone who frauds' he translates as 'if there be anyone who transgresses';
  ወመባእሂ፡ጽዒንየ፡ዘአውረድኩ፡በአምኀራ, which I translates as ' I loaded offerings that I brought from ʾAmḥarā' he translates as 'and offerings which I brought down through Amhara on pack animals (marked with a question-mark by a translator himself)';
  ዘኢይትፈታሕ, which I translate as 'This [transgression] can not be released' he translates as 'in such a way that it cannot be revoked';
